chmod - used to change file or directory permissions
      [r-Read-4]
      [w-Write-2]
      [x-Execute-1]
      [- file]
    1) Symbolic way- chmod [who][operator][permission] file
         Who	Meaning
         u	   User      rw-(can read and write,cannot execute)
         g	   Group     ---(cannot read,write,execute)
         o	   Others    r--(can read,cannot write,cannot execute)
         a	   All
         Operators:
         +	 Add permission
         -	 Remove permission
         =   Set exact permission
         [chmod u+x snow.txt = -rwx---r--]  
         [chmod u-w filename = -r-x---r--]
   2) Numeric way - chmod XYZ file
         X = User
         Y = Group
         Z = Others
     [chmod 755 filename = rwxr-xr-x]
      7 = 4+2+1 = rwx
      5 = 4+0+1 = r-x
      5 = 4+0+1 = r-x
chmod 755 hlo.txt:  gives permission based on number system
Owner → rwx (7)
Group → r-x (5)
Others → r-x (5)
chmod g-w file.txt : remove write permission to group
chmod -r 755 folder/ : recursive permission change
chgown owner filename: to change the owner of the file
chgown owner:group filename: to change owner and grp of the file
chgown -r name folder/ : change the owner of the given folder and its inside files

chgrp group filename: to change the group of the file
chgrp -r name folder/ : change the group of the given folder and its inside files

unmask : Defines the default permissions for newly created files and directories.
